{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857887205,"sessionID":"ses_286a086e6ffehzsGtZnxuer4fi","part":{"id":"prt_d7960e398001DZ2pIWCXbcBIOj","messageID":"msg_d7960cbba001FXyNT4qzthy1SB","sessionID":"ses_286a086e6ffehzsGtZnxuer4fi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1860e0cfa2864eb0b5b61a1f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","offset":1524},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1524: type redisStore struct {\n1525:     cli                  *redisv9.Client\n1526:     sessionPrefix        string  // \"session:\"\n1527:     expiryIndexKey       string  // \"session:expiry\"\n1528:     lastActivityIndexKey string  // \"session:last_activity\"\n1529: }\n1530: ```\n1531: \n1532: **Connection Configuration:**\n1533: \n1534: | Env Variable | Required | Description |\n1535: |--------------|----------|-------------|\n1536: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | Server address |\n1537: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | Password (*unless REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false) |\n1538: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | Default: \"redis\" |\n1539: \n1540: **Operation Mappings:**\n1541: \n1542: | Method | Redis Commands |\n1543: |--------|----------------|\n1544: | `Ping` | PING → expect \"PONG\" |\n1545: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | GET session:{id} |\n1546: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity |\n1547: | `UpdateSandbox` | SET key value XX |\n1548: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity |\n1549: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | ZRANGEBYSCORE with LIMIT, then GET pipeline |\n1550: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity, then GET pipeline |\n1551: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | GET (verify exists), then ZADD |\n1552: \n1553: ### 5.2 Valkey Implementation\n1554: \n1555: **Struct:**\n1556: \n1557: ```go\n1558: type valkeyStore struct {\n1559:     cli                  valkey.Client\n1560:     sessionPrefix        string  // \"session:\"\n1561:     expiryIndexKey       string  // \"session:expiry\"\n1562:     lastActivityIndexKey string  // \"session:last_activity\"\n1563: }\n1564: ```\n1565: \n1566: **Connection Configuration:**\n1567: \n1568: | Env Variable | Required | Description |\n1569: |--------------|----------|-------------|\n1570: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated addresses |\n1571: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | Password (*unless VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false) |\n1572: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | \"true\" enables DisableCache |\n1573: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | \"true\" enables ForceSingleClient |\n1574: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be \"valkey\" | Case-insensitive |\n1575: \n1576: **Operation Mappings:**\n1577: \n1578: | Method | Valkey API |\n1579: |--------|------------|\n1580: | `Ping` | B().Ping() → \"PONG\" |\n1581: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | B().Get().Key(key), IsValkeyNil → ErrNotFound |\n1582: | `StoreSandbox` | DoMulti: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity |\n1583: | `UpdateSandbox` | SET ... XX, verify response == \"OK\" |\n1584: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | DoMulti: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity |\n1585: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same pattern on last_activity key |\n1586: \n1587: ### 5.3 ZSET Score Semantics\n1588: \n1589: - **Expiry index:** Score = `float64(sandboxInfo.ExpiresAt.Unix())`\n1590: - **Last activity:**\n1591:   - On store: `float64(time.Now().Unix())`\n1592:   - On update: `float64(at.Unix())` or `time.Now()` if `at` is zero\n1593: \n1594: ---\n1595: \n1596: ## 6. Error Handling\n1597: \n1598: ### 6.1 Error Types\n1599: \n1600: | Error | Condition |\n1601: |-------|-----------|\n1602: | `ErrNotFound` | Session key does not exist; ZSET member missing |\n1603: | \"sandbox is nil\" | StoreSandbox called with nil |\n1604: | \"key not exists\" | UpdateSandbox on non-existent key |\n1605: | \"password required\" | Missing password without _REQUIRED=false |\n1606: \n1607: ### 6.2 Precondition Validation\n1608: \n1609: | Operation | Validation |\n1610: |-----------|------------|\n1611: | `StoreSandbox` | Reject nil sandbox, reject zero ExpiresAt |\n1612: | `UpdateSandbox` | Use SET with XX flag (key must exist) |\n1613: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | Verify session key exists before ZADD |\n1614: | `ListExpired/Inactive` | If limit <= 0, return nil, nil |\n1615: \n1616: ---\n1617: \n1618: ## 7. Testing Strategy\n1619: \n1620: ### 7.1 Unit Tests\n1621: \n1622: | Component | Test Coverage |\n1623: |-----------|---------------|\n1624: | Store Interface | Mock implementation verification |\n1625: | Redis Store | All CRUD operations |\n1626: | Valkey Store | All CRUD operations |\n1627: | Key Construction | sessionKey(), prefix constants |\n1628: | Error Conditions | ErrNotFound paths |\n1629: \n1630: ### 7.2 Integration Tests\n1631: \n1632: | Scenario | Approach |\n1633: |----------|----------|\n1634: | Real Redis | Docker container, test suite |\n1635: | Real Valkey | Docker container, test suite |\n1636: | Key Schema | Verify actual keys in Redis/Valkey |\n1637: \n1638: ### 7.3 Edge Cases\n1639: \n1640: - Empty session ID on UpdateSessionLastActivity → error\n1641: - Zero time on UpdateSessionLastActivity → use time.Now()\n1642: - Orphan ZSET member (no document) → skip without error\n1643: - Concurrent Storage() calls → only one initialization\n1644: \n1645: ---\n1646: \n1647: ## 8. Dependencies\n1648: \n1649: ```go\n1650: import (\n1651:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n1652:     \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n1653:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n1654:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n1655: )\n1656: ```\n1657: \n1658: ---\n1659: \n1660: ## 9. Configuration Flow\n1661: \n1662: ```\n1663: Storage() \n1664:     → initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n1665:         → Read STORE_TYPE (default: \"redis\")\n1666:         → Validate required env vars\n1667:         → Create provider (Redis or Valkey)\n1668:         → Return provider singleton\n1669: ```\n1670: \n1671: ### Provider Selection\n1672: \n1673: | STORE_TYPE | Implementation |\n1674: |------------|----------------|\n1675: | \"redis\" (default) | redisStore |\n1676: | \"valkey\" | valkeyStore |\n1677: | other | fail initialization |\n1678: \n1679: ---\n1680: \n1681: ## 10. Migration Path\n1682: \n1683: If migrating from Redis to Valkey:\n1684: \n1685: 1. Set `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n1686: 2. Set `VALKEY_ADDR` (cluster addresses)\n1687: 3. Set `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n1688: 4. Optionally set `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n1689: 5. Ensure cluster mode if using multiple Valkey nodes\n1690: \n1691: Key compatibility is maintained across both backends (same key schema, same ZSET semantics).\n\n(End of file - total 1691 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"type redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string  // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string  // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string  // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n```\n\n**Connection Configuration:**\n\n| Env Variable | Required | Description |\n|--------------|----------|-------------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | Server address |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | Password (*unless REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false) |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | Default: \"redis\" |\n\n**Operation Mappings:**\n\n| Method | Redis Commands |\n|--------|----------------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775857887183,"end":1775857887202}}}}
